{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SOP/voronoifracture", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "internal": "primgroup_extract_piece_ql", "version": "1", "namespace": "qLib"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["PrimGroups Extract Piece qL"], "extent": [54, 86]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "strong", "text": ["interface version 1"]}], "extent": [86, 110]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Helper operator for ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib::primgroups_extract_tool_ql::1", "type": "link", "text": ["PrimGroups Extract Tool qL"], "exists": true}, " to extract geometry pieces."], "extent": [110, 239]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This is a helper node that encompasses multiple operations as a single node, such as:"], "extent": [239, 326]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["Object Merge"]}, ", to fetch a single primitive group (piece) from a single source geometry collective"], "extent": [326, 427]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["Attribute Promote"]}, ", to change certain attribute classifications for the extracted piece."], "extent": [427, 520]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["(This operator is usually created by the\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib::primgroups_extract_tool_ql::1", "type": "link", "text": ["PrimGroups Extract Tool"], "exists": true}, ".)"], "extent": [520, 636]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Attribute Promotions"], "extent": [636, 665], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This feature allows attributes to be imported as ", {"type": "em", "text": ["shape attributes"]}, " in Maya through the alembic format."], "extent": [665, 771]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Once a single SOP geometry is extracted as multiple OBJ geometry pieces, each piece can internally\npromote certain attributes to ", {"type": "em", "text": ["detail"]}, " class. The Maya alembic importer will recreate these attributes\nas attributes on the Maya ", {"type": "em", "text": ["geometry shape"]}, " (it\u2019s also called ", {"type": "q", "text": ["extra attribute"]}, " in Maya terminology)."], "extent": [771, 1075]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["These extra attributes can be useful for passing all kinds of information \u2013\nthe default settings on this node contains promotions for 3 attributes\n(", {"type": "code", "text": ["SG_surfaceShader"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["SG_displaceShader"]}, " and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["SG_volumeShader"]}, ".)"], "extent": [1075, 1289]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["These can contain shader names \u2013 so a MEL script could go through all imported objects and\nperform the appropriate shading assignments."], "extent": [1289, 1427]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["With a little MEL scripting support from the Maya side, geometry with shader name information\ncan be easily passed between Maya and Houdini (eliminating the need of assigning shaders by\nhand in Maya after each import)."], "extent": [1427, 1648]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1648, 1653], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["In order to set up your own permanent settings (for attribute promotions),\n    set up the parameters on a single Extract Piece node, then use the\n    ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Save as Permanent Defaults"]}, " menu item from the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["gearbox"]}, " menu of a Parameter panel."], "extent": [1653, 1893]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["From that point, each ", {"type": "em", "text": ["new"]}, " extracted piece will inherit your settings.\n    (You might need to rebuild existing piece-extract node networks.)"], "extent": [1893, 2042]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2042, 2054], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Object, Group, Transform"], "extent": [2054, 2084], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Regular Object Merge SOP parameters\n        (initialized by the\n        ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib::primgroups_extract_tool_ql::1", "type": "link", "text": ["PrimGroups Extract Tool"], "exists": true}, "\n        that created this particular operator)."], "extent": [2084, 2284]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Attribute Promotions"], "extent": [2284, 2310], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["A list of attribute promotion operations."], "extent": [2310, 2362]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "todo", "container": true, "type": "todo_section", "indent": 0, "text": ["To Do"], "role": "section", "extent": [2362, 2374], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Wildcard-based attribute promotion"], "extent": [2374, 2415]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Make sure all SG_ attribs are spelled right"], "extent": [2415, 2465]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Add other example attribs to the default list (e.g. arnold volume step size, etc.)"], "extent": [2465, 2554]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["\u2026"], "extent": [2554, 2566]}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2566, 2575], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib::primgroups_extract_tool_ql::1", "type": "link", "text": ["PrimGroups Extract Tool qL SOP"], "exists": true}], "extent": [2575, 2661]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}, {"level": 1, "id": "relnotes", "container": true, "type": "relnotes_section", "indent": 0, "text": ["Release Notes"], "role": "section", "extent": [2661, 2685], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["interface version 1"]}, " \u2014"], "extent": [2685, 2717]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["2014-10-03"], "extent": [2717, 2733], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Fixed typo (displaceShader->displacementShader)"], "extent": [2733, 2790]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["2014-07-24"], "extent": [2790, 2806], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["First version."], "extent": [2806, 2830]}], "container": true}], "container": true}]}], "title": ["PrimGroups Extract Piece qL"], "summary": ["Helper operator for ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib::primgroups_extract_tool_ql::1", "type": "link", "text": ["PrimGroups Extract Tool qL"], "exists": true}, " to extract geometry pieces."]}